# Case study layout

Use this hierarchy for all project case study body content inside `ProjectLayout`.

## Page shell

- One outer wrapper: `container py-5 d-flex flex-column gap-5`
- Place `<Divider />` between L1 sections (not before the first or after the last)
- `ProjectLayout` still provides hero + divider above body content

## Levels

| Level | Element | Classes | Notes |
|-------|---------|---------|-------|
| L1 | `<section>` | `d-flex flex-column gap-4` | `h4` title with `id` for TOC/hash |
| L2 | `<div>` | `d-flex flex-column gap-2` | `h6` title with `id`; group siblings in `d-flex flex-column gap-3` |
| L3 | `<div>` | `ps-3 py-2 border-start d-flex flex-column gap-1` | `h6` title with `id` |

## Template

```jsx
<div className="container py-5 d-flex flex-column gap-5">
  <section className="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
    <h4 id="section-slug">L1 Section Title</h4>
    <p>Intro copy directly under L1.</p>
    <div className="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
      <div className="d-flex flex-column gap-2">
        <h6 id="subsection-slug">L2 Section Title</h6>
        <p>L2 body copy.</p>
        <div className="ps-3 py-2 border-start d-flex flex-column gap-1">
          <h6 id="subsubsection-slug">L3 Section Title</h6>
          <p>L3 body copy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Divider />
  <section className="d-flex flex-column gap-4">...</section>
</div>
```

## Rules

- L1 titles: `h4` only. L2/L3 titles: `h6` only. Never `p.lead` for section titles.
- Put `id` on the heading element (`h4` or `h6`), not on a wrapper.
- Images, lists, and grids stay inside the section level they belong to (after relevant copy).
- Every image/placeholder keeps the `border` utility.
- Do not add extra `container` or `py-5` on individual L1 sections.
